wifi

Class WifiConnection

  • java.lang.Object
    • wifi.WifiConnection

  • public class WifiConnection
extends Object
    This class opens a wifi connection, waits for the data and then allows access to the data after closing the wifi socket. It should be used by calling the constructor which will automatically wait for data without any further user command Then, once completed, it will allow access to an instance of the Transmission class which has access to all of the data needed
